# Mycelium — example environment file.
#
# Copy this to `.env` and fill in real values:   cp .env.example .env
# `.env` is git-ignored (never committed); `.env.example` IS committed and MUST pass the gitleaks
# secret scan — so every value here is an OBVIOUSLY-FAKE placeholder, never a real credential.
#
# Honesty / house rules (CLAUDE.md):
#   - This file is IN scope for gitleaks (NOT allowlisted): it is a template that must stay clean.
#   - Placeholders use a clearly-fake sentinel (`REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_*`) that does not match a real
#     key shape closely enough to be a credential, yet documents the expected variable.
#   - Add a variable here whenever the toolchain learns to read a new one — this doubles as the
#     canonical list of environment inputs.

# ── LLM / agent harness ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The Grok / xAI harness reads XAI_API_KEY (preferred) or GROK_API_KEY. Get a key from the xAI
# console and paste it here in your local `.env` (never commit the real value).
XAI_API_KEY=xai-REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_KEY
# Alias some tooling reads instead of XAI_API_KEY; set whichever your harness expects.
GROK_API_KEY=xai-REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_KEY
# Optional: override the xAI API base URL (defaults to the provider's public endpoint when unset).
# XAI_BASE_URL=https://api.x.ai/v1

# Optional: Anthropic API key, if you drive the Claude-based tooling locally rather than via the IDE.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_KEY

# ── Installer knobs (consumed by scripts/install.sh and scripts/install-tools.sh) ──────────────────
# Components to install when none are passed as flags (whitespace- or comma-separated):
#   rust python checks hooks mlir   (mlir is opt-in; see ADR-019).
# MYC_INSTALL_COMPONENTS=rust python checks hooks
#
# Skip the slow optional cargo introspection tools (cargo-modules/depgraph/public-api) during setup
# so a cloud Setup-script run stays inside its cache-build budget. Set to 1 to skip.
# MYCELIUM_SKIP_OPTIONAL_CARGO=0

# ── Misc ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Force-disable ANSI colour in the check/install scripts' output (they already auto-detect a TTY).
# NO_COLOR=1
